In Python, a basic recursive Fibonacci function is:

```python
def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= {{c1::1}}:
        return n
    return fibonacci({{c2::n - 1}}) + fibonacci({{c3::n - 2}})
```

The time complexity is {{c4::O(2^n)}} due to overlapping subproblems.

